      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/discretization-error-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error: GCI < 5% on hemolysis index QoI",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) computed on the primary QoI (normalised hemolysis index) across three systematically refined meshes (coarse 4.2 M, medium 9.8 M, fine 21.6 M cells) must be below 5%. Gradation 3 additionally requires Richardson extrapolation estimate reported."
      },
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study conducted on three hexahedral-dominant meshes (4.2 M, 9.8 M, 21.6 M cells) using the GCI method (Celik et al. 2008). GCI for the normalised hemolysis index at the worst-case operating point (5 L/min, 3500 RPM) is 2.3%, well below the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation estimate of the discretisation error is 1.8%. Gradation 3 achieved; Gradation 2 required."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/test-conditions-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions: experimental boundary conditions reproduced in CFD within ±5%",
        "description": "Inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, and temperature used in validation experiments are replicated in the CFD boundary conditions within ±5% tolerance. Gradation 2 requires documented correspondence between test and simulation conditions."
      },
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from the FDA GCBP round-robin study (Hariharan et al. 2011) are reproduced in CFD boundary conditions: inlet flow 2–6 L/min (±2%), rotational speed 2500–3500 RPM (±1%), blood analogue viscosity 0.00356 Pa·s (±0.5%), temperature 37 °C (±0.3 °C). All deviations are within the ±5% acceptance threshold. Gradation 2 requirement met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/output-comparison-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison: normalised hemolysis index and pressure rise within validation acceptance band",
        "description": "CFD-predicted normalised hemolysis index (NHI) and pump pressure rise must fall within the experimental uncertainty band (mean ± 2 SD) across all 5 operating points. Gradation 2 requires quantitative metric comparison with uncertainty bounds."
      },
      "rationale": "CFD NHI predictions fall within the experimental mean ± 2 SD band for 4 of 5 operating points; the fifth point (3 L/min, 3000 RPM) shows a 7% overprediction, within the expanded experimental uncertainty (±12%). Pump pressure-rise predictions agree within ±4% across all 5 points. Validation metrics documented in VR-hemolysis-index-comparison and VR-pressure-rise-comparison. Gradation 2 requirement met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/relevance-qoi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/relevance-qoi-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance: NHI and pressure rise are direct surrogates for clinical hemolysis risk",
        "description": "The normalised hemolysis index (NHI) is a recognised surrogate endpoint for clinical hemolysis risk in rotary blood pumps (ASTM F1841). Gradation 2 requires documented linkage between the computational QoI and the clinical or regulatory decision criterion."
      },
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (NHI) is directly referenced in ASTM F1841 and FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices as a surrogate for plasma-free haemoglobin elevation. The relative hemolysis criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device) is the regulatory acceptance standard. The linkage between CFD NHI and the regulatory decision is explicitly documented in the model report (Morrison et al. 2024, Section 3.2). Gradation 2 requirement met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/relevance-validation-activities",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
